   <conbody>
      <p otherprops="typeS" class="- topic/p ">A single system consists of a single unit supplying
the load.</p>
      <p otherprops="typeR" class="- topic/p ">A redundant system consists of two units working
together in parallel to supply a common load. Each unit can supply
the full load if needed.</p>
      <p platform="PxW" class="- topic/p ">In an uninterruptible power supply (UPS) a rectifier
converts alternating current (AC) from the rectifier mains to direct
current (DC). The DC circuit charges the battery bank. The inverter
converts back DC to AC that supplies the load. If the rectifier mains
becomes unavailable, the load is supplied without interruption by
the battery bank. <ph otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/ph "> The bypass can
supply the load if the inverter is inoperable.</ph>
      </p>
      <p platform="WxW" class="- topic/p ">In an inverter system an inverter converts direct
current (DC) to alternating current (AC) that supplies the load.<ph otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS" class="- topic/ph "> The bypass can supply the load if
the inverter is inoperable.</ph>
      </p>
